HEADWORD: Pulmonarian
<hw>Pul"mo*na"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any arachnid that breathes by lunglike organs, as the spiders and
scorpions. Also used adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

